# waddle_controller tests

- Co-locate tests as `*.test.ts` beside the module under `src/auth/`, `src/api/`, `src/storage/`, `src/util/`, or `src/constants/`.
- Use Vitest (`describe` / `it` / `expect` / `vi`); `vitest.setup.ts` clears `localStorage` and `sessionStorage` after each test.
- Mock `fetch` with `vi.stubGlobal('fetch', …)` for API modules; avoid real network I/O.
- For time-dependent session expiry, use `vi.useFakeTimers()` in `sessions` tests.
- Page-level UI: prefer React Testing Library in `*.test.tsx` when adding component coverage; keep business logic in `.ts` modules with unit tests.

Before pushing controller test changes:

```bash
cd apps/waddle_controller
npm run lint
npm run test:coverage
npm run coverage:check
```
